cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DL

This paper deals with the analysis of unstructured textual data, specifically news and blogs, using natural language processing and semantic annotation techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with techniques for retrieving relevant information from unstructured data. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing and semantic annotation, which are key techniques in the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions the use of a scalable architecture for real-time processing, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper mentions the use of visualizations to present the data, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
